---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'quick-verdict', text: 'Quick Verdict', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Side-by-Side Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'safetywing', text: 'SafetyWing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'img-global', text: 'IMG Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'cigna-global', text: 'Cigna Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'nomad-needs', text: 'Digital Nomad-Specific Needs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Which Is Best For You?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'SafetyWing Review', href: '/providers/safetywing' },
  { title: 'IMG Global Review', href: '/providers/img-global' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Digital Nomad Insurance', href: '/best/digital-nomad-insurance' },
  { title: 'Remote Worker Insurance', href: '/best/remote-worker-insurance' },
];

const mainComparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
];

const mainComparisonRows = [
  { feature: 'Insurance Type', safetywing: 'Travel medical', img: 'Health insurance', cigna: 'Premium health' },
  { feature: 'Coverage Limit', safetywing: '$250,000', img: '$1M - $8M', cigna: 'Unlimited' },
  { feature: 'Monthly Flexibility', safetywing: 'Yes', img: 'No', cigna: 'No' },
  { feature: 'Home Country Cover', safetywing: '30 days/90', img: 'Optional', cigna: 'Full optional' },
  { feature: 'Pre-existing Conditions', safetywing: 'Not covered', img: 'Underwritten', cigna: 'Underwritten' },
  { feature: 'Multi-Country Living', safetywing: 'Excellent', img: 'Good', cigna: 'Excellent' },
  { feature: 'App Experience', safetywing: 'Good', img: 'Basic', cigna: 'Excellent' },
  { feature: 'Best For', safetywing: 'Budget nomads', img: 'Mid-range needs', cigna: 'Full coverage' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Single, Age 25', safetywing: '$45-55/mo', img: '$80-150/mo', cigna: '$200-350/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 35', safetywing: '$55-70/mo', img: '$120-200/mo', cigna: '$280-450/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 45', safetywing: '$80-100/mo', img: '$180-280/mo', cigna: '$400-600/mo' },
  { profile: 'Couple, Age 30', safetywing: '$100-130/mo', img: '$200-320/mo', cigna: '$500-750/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="SafetyWing vs IMG vs Cigna: Best Digital Nomad Insurance 2026"
  description="Compare the top 3 insurance options for digital nomads: SafetyWing, IMG Global, and Cigna Global. From budget travel medical to premium health insurance."
  headline="SafetyWing vs IMG vs Cigna: Digital Nomad Insurance Compared"
  subheadline="The three tiers of nomad coverage—budget travel medical, mid-range health insurance, and premium global coverage. Pick based on your lifestyle."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes"
  ctaButtonHref="/get-quotes"
>
  <h2 id="quick-verdict">Quick Verdict</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
    <div class="bg-amber-50 border-2 border-amber-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Budget Pick</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">SafetyWing</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">$45/mo starting. Built for nomads. Monthly subscription, no commitment. Perfect for young, healthy travelers.</p>
      <a href="/go/safetywing" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get SafetyWing Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-neutral-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Mid-Range</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">IMG Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Real health insurance at competitive prices. Flexible deductibles. Good for those wanting more than travel medical.</p>
      <a href="/go/img-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-neutral-700 hover:bg-neutral-800 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get IMG Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border-2 border-primary-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Premium Choice</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Unlimited coverage. Best app and service. For nomads who want the best and can afford it.</p>
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    Digital nomads face unique insurance challenges: changing locations, crossing borders, no permanent address. These three represent the spectrum of solutions—from SafetyWing's nomad-focused travel medical to Cigna's comprehensive global coverage.
  </p>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={mainComparisonColumns} rows={mainComparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="safetywing">SafetyWing</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Built for Nomads</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Monthly Billing</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">No Commitment</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    SafetyWing was literally built for digital nomads. It's the only option here with monthly subscription billing—start and stop coverage as needed. At $45/month starting, it's the entry point for nomad coverage. But remember: it's travel medical insurance, not comprehensive health insurance.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Only $45/mo starting price</li>
    <li>Monthly subscription—no annual commitment</li>
    <li>Designed specifically for nomad lifestyle</li>
    <li>Covers 180+ countries seamlessly</li>
    <li>30 days US/home country coverage included</li>
    <li>Simple signup, instant coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Travel medical, not health insurance</li>
    <li>$250K limit (low for serious illness)</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions excluded</li>
    <li>Limited routine care</li>
    <li>Mental health: crisis only</li>
    <li>No maternity except emergencies</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Young, healthy nomads who want affordable emergency coverage with maximum flexibility. Those just starting their nomad journey who need basic protection.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/safetywing" class="inline-block bg-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get SafetyWing Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/safetywing" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="img-global">IMG Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-neutral-200 text-neutral-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Real Health Insurance</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-neutral-200 text-neutral-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Flexible Plans</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-neutral-200 text-neutral-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Good Value</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    IMG bridges the gap between travel medical and premium insurance. It's actual health insurance with higher limits, comprehensive coverage, and pre-existing condition options—at prices nomads can stomach. The middle ground for those who've outgrown SafetyWing but can't justify Cigna.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Real health insurance coverage</li>
    <li>Up to $8M annual limit</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions considered</li>
    <li>Flexible deductible options</li>
    <li>Routine care included</li>
    <li>Competitive pricing for coverage level</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Annual commitment required</li>
    <li>Less nomad-specific than SafetyWing</li>
    <li>App and digital experience basic</li>
    <li>Mental health coverage limited</li>
    <li>Claims can be slower</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Nomads ready to upgrade from travel medical to real health insurance. Those with moderate healthcare needs or minor pre-existing conditions.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/img-global" class="inline-block bg-neutral-700 hover:bg-neutral-800 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get IMG Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/img-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="cigna-global">Cigna Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Premium Coverage</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best App</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Unlimited Benefits</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Cigna Global is the gold standard for expat insurance. Unlimited coverage, 1.5M+ provider network, best-in-class app and service. For nomads earning well who want the best protection available. Yes, it costs 4-5x SafetyWing—but you get real, comprehensive coverage.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Unlimited annual coverage</li>
    <li>1.5M+ provider network worldwide</li>
    <li>Best app in the industry</li>
    <li>Fast claims processing</li>
    <li>Comprehensive mental health benefits</li>
    <li>Full home country coverage optional</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>4-5x more expensive than SafetyWing</li>
    <li>Annual commitment required</li>
    <li>Overkill for young, healthy nomads</li>
    <li>US coverage adds significant cost</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Established nomads earning good income who want the best coverage. Those with pre-existing conditions or ongoing healthcare needs. Nomads who value premium service.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/cigna-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare All Three"
    description="Get personalized quotes from SafetyWing, IMG, and Cigna based on your specific nomad needs."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing Comparison</h2>

  <p>
    The price spread is significant. SafetyWing costs $45-100/month, IMG runs $80-280/month, and Cigna starts around $200/month and goes up from there. What you're paying for: coverage limits, network size, and service quality.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
    *Estimated ranges for plans excluding US coverage. Actual prices depend on age, health history, and selected coverage options.
  </p>

  <h2 id="nomad-needs">Digital Nomad-Specific Needs</h2>

  <p>
    Digital nomads have unique requirements that traditional expat insurance doesn't always address:
  </p>

  <h3>Multi-Country Living</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>SafetyWing:</strong> Excellent—designed for moving between countries constantly</li>
    <li><strong>IMG:</strong> Good—covers most countries, need to declare residence changes</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Excellent—seamless global coverage, easy to update location</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Home Country Visits</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>SafetyWing:</strong> 30 days per 90-day period included (US coverage limited)</li>
    <li><strong>IMG:</strong> Optional add-on for home country coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Full home country coverage available (costs more)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>No Fixed Address</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>SafetyWing:</strong> No problem—designed for address-free lifestyle</li>
    <li><strong>IMG:</strong> Needs a residence address on file</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Flexible—can use any address where you spend time</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Monthly Flexibility</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>SafetyWing:</strong> Only option with true monthly billing</li>
    <li><strong>IMG:</strong> Annual plans only</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Annual plans only</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="best-for">Which Is Best For You?</h2>

  <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose SafetyWing if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Are under 40 and healthy</li>
        <li>Want maximum flexibility (month-to-month)</li>
        <li>Are on a tight budget</li>
        <li>Just need emergency coverage</li>
        <li>Move frequently between countries</li>
        <li>Are willing to accept limited coverage for lower cost</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose IMG Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Want real health insurance, not travel medical</li>
        <li>Have moderate budget ($100-300/mo)</li>
        <li>Need routine care covered</li>
        <li>Have minor pre-existing conditions</li>
        <li>Are settling in one region for a while</li>
        <li>Want more coverage than SafetyWing without premium prices</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Cigna Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Earn enough to afford premium coverage</li>
        <li>Have ongoing healthcare needs</li>
        <li>Want the best app and customer service</li>
        <li>Need comprehensive mental health coverage</li>
        <li>Have pre-existing conditions requiring coverage</li>
        <li>Value peace of mind over cost savings</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Can I start with SafetyWing and upgrade later?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, but timing matters. Anything that happens while on SafetyWing becomes pre-existing for your next policy. If you're healthy now, SafetyWing is fine. But if you develop a condition, upgrading becomes harder. Consider this when deciding.
  </p>

  <h3>Does SafetyWing count as health insurance for visa requirements?</h3>
  <p>
    Usually no. Most Digital Nomad Visas require "health insurance," not travel medical insurance. SafetyWing may work for some countries, but many (like Portugal, Spain, Czech Republic) require comprehensive health coverage. Check visa requirements carefully.
  </p>

  <h3>Which is best for US citizens?</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing has limited US coverage. IMG has optional US coverage. Cigna offers full US coverage at additional cost. If you'll be spending significant time in the US, factor this into your decision—US healthcare is expensive.
  </p>

  <h3>What about coworking and remote work injuries?</h3>
  <p>
    All three cover accidents regardless of where they happen. But if you need workers' compensation-style coverage, none of these provide it. That's a separate product entirely.
  </p>

  <h3>How do claims work while traveling?</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing: Submit receipts for reimbursement (simple process). IMG: Mix of direct billing and reimbursement. Cigna: Best direct billing network, minimal out-of-pocket in most places. The more you pay, the smoother claims become.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Prices and coverage details change. We are not insurance brokers. Verify current information directly with each provider before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
